|image1    = Tutorial Snack Dash 1.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_1004001.png>-<Tutorial Snack Dash 1.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text1     = Snack Dash is an obstacle race event spontaneously organized by the creations, where {{Color|h|nobold=1|8}} players can participate as spectators and {{Color|h|nobold=1|cheer}} for the contestants.
|image2    = Tutorial Snack Dash 2.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_1004002.png>-<Tutorial Snack Dash 2.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text2     = Cheering requires {{Color|h|nobold=1|Bounce-Bounce Snacks}}, but at the end of each round, if the contestant you cheered for ranks in the {{Color|h|nobold=1|top three}}, you'll receive massive snack rewards based on their winning profits.
|image3    = Tutorial Snack Dash 3.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_1004003.png>-<Tutorial Snack Dash 3.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text3     = During the match, players can use {{Color|h|nobold=1|arena items}} to influence the game. After using any item, {{Color|h|nobold=1|all items}} will enter cooldown.
|image4    = Tutorial Snack Dash 4.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_1004004.png>-<Tutorial Snack Dash 4.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text4     = After each match, you'll earn {{Color|h|nobold=1|Spectator Points}}. Higher-tier matches award more points, and you can claim Spectator Rewards by accumulating points.
|image5    = Tutorial Snack Dash 5.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_1004005.png>-<Tutorial Snack Dash 5.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text5     = After watching your first match in the advanced arena, {{Color|h|nobold=1|Snack Exchange}} will be unlocked, allowing you to exchange excess "Bounce-Bounce Snacks" for rewards such as Trick Snacks and Tears of Souls.
}}